  "prompt": "How do you buy a used car?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to buy a used car:\n\n1. Determine your budget\n- Consider purchase price and ongoing costs\n- Get pre-approved for financing if needed\n\n2. Research and decide on the type of car you want\n- Consider reliability, fuel efficiency, maintenance costs\n- Read consumer reviews and ratings\n\n3. Find potential cars\n- Online marketplaces (Craigslist, AutoTrader)\n- Dealerships\n- Private sellers\n- Used car websites\n\n4. Check the car's history\n- Get a vehicle history report (Carfax)\n- Check for accidents, previous ownership, maintenance records\n\n5. Inspect the car\n- Look for signs of damage or wear\n- Check exterior, interior, and mechanical condition\n- Take a test drive\n- Have a mechanic perform a professional inspection\n\n6. Negotiate the price\n- Compare prices with similar models\n- Use vehicle history and condition as negotiation points\n\n7. Complete the purchase\n- Verify all paperwork\n- Get title and registration\n- Transfer ownership\n- Obtain insurance\n\n8. Additional tips\n- Don't rush\n- Be prepared to walk away\n- Get everything in writing\n- Understand warranty or return policies",
